creator: Ray Cummings; Charles Willard Diffin; Jack Williamson; Harl Vincent; F. V. W. Mason
description:
LibriVox recording of Astounding Stories 15, March 1931 by Ray Cummings; Charles Willard Diffin; Jack Williamson; Harl Vincent; F. V. W. Mason .
Read in English by Catherine Russell; Larry Wilson; Mark Nelson; Alan Winterrowd; Douglas Taylor; Beth Thomas
This issue includes "When the Mountain Came to Miramar" by Charles W. Diffin, "Beyond the Vanishing Point" by Ray Cummings, "Terrors Unseen" by Harl Vincent, the conclusion of "Phalanxes of Atlans" by F. V. W. Mason, and "The Meteor Girl" by Jack Williamson. - Summary by Bill Boerst
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
